{"word":"ἐπιμελής","slug":"ἐπιμελής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιμελής</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>μέλομαι</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>careful</i> or <i>anxious about, put in charge of</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:— <el>τὸ ἐπιμελές τινος  ἐπιμέλεια</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>careful, attentive</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>cared for, an object of care</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>ἐπιμελές μοι ἦν</el> it was my <i>business</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic<p/></div>"}]}